originalText.text: Very lovely! What a church should be like: plain and simple, down to earth, unpretentious, with a focus on the Word. In addition, a sound amplification system which notably, unlike the majority of churches in Harlem, is used to facilitate communication, not piledrive it into your ears at dangerous unhealthful 137-decibel levels. Every church has its own formal traditions and ceremonial flourishes and this one takes it further with a pastor who tends to her flock lovingly addressing them as one would her own children. Probably the finest heart-felt Mother's Day sermon (Sunday, May 8, 2016) I have ever had the privilege of experiencing.
